<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-05-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-05-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="203" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d203">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Adams</persName>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 601.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-05-19"><hi rend="italic">May</hi> 19, 1863.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I enclose for your information the copy of
                            a note of the 12th instant addressed by this department to Lord Lyons,
                            relative to an impression in England that it is the intention of this
                            government, by captures without cause, by delays of adjudication, and by
                            wanton imprisonment of the masters and, part of the crews of captured
                            vessels, to put a stop to the British trade to Matamoras altogether.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis Adams</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>